    <note>Zhao(1) Gongcheng [364] According to the funerary inscription of his great granddaughter-in-law (born Tang(1) married to Zhao(1) Shikan [14821] [q.v.]), Gongcheng was Zhenjiang, Jintan county magistrate and after his tour of duty, the residents erected a shrine (ci or deity temple) in his honor. His son, Yanxun [14819], seems to have moved to Duchang county, but his grandson, Liangfu [14820], was married to born Chu(2), an illustrious lineage (wangzu) of Jintan and probably moved here during this generation since two of his sons, Shikan and Shizuo [14823], are considered as Jintan residents, even though Shikan is also still listed in the Jiangxi TZ jinshi list as a Duchang county resident. Jiangxi TZ, 22.7b; XNYL, 174.3b, 175.1a, 176.8b. Lineage source SS, 234.10a (PRC ed. 234.7763). CBD, 4, 3414-5.</note>
